 {"id":"phage_explorer-3r5p","title":"Web mobile: top QuickStats bar clipped/unusable (swipe conflict)","description":"## User-facing problem
On mobile, the top metadata/status surface (QuickStats bar: Length / GC / Genes / etc.) is effectively **cut off / unusable**. Users try to horizontal-swipe to see the hidden stats, but the gesture is intercepted by global phage swipe navigation, making the bar feel broken and causing accidental phage changes.

## Root cause
`App.tsx` installs a global touch-swipe handler on `#main-content` to navigate prev/next phage. The handler intentionally ignores certain interactive/gesture surfaces (sequence view, 3D, buttons, etc.) but currently does **not** ignore the horizontally scrollable `.quick-stats` bar.

## Goals
- Allow horizontal scrolling of the QuickStats bar without triggering phage navigation.
- Preserve the global swipe-to-change-phage gesture everywhere it makes sense (background areas).
- Avoid regressions: sequence/3D should continue to block global swipe.

## Proposed implementation
- Update the `shouldIgnoreTarget()` selector in `App.tsx` to include `.quick-stats` (and any related status surfaces like `.db-status-bar` if applicable).
- Optional polish: add a subtle fade/affordance indicating the bar is horizontally scrollable on mobile.

## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Swiping left/right on QuickStats scrolls the bar horizontally (when overflowed).
- [ ] Swiping left/right on empty background areas still changes phage.
- [ ] No accidental phage navigation when interacting with QuickStats.

## Test plan
- Unit/integration (preferred): simulate touchstart/touchend on elements within `.quick-stats` and assert the swipe handler does not call next/prev.
